window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>They say the wrath of a female scorned could rival that of the gods. But the wrath of two vengeful queens will set the realm ablaze.</b></p> <p>First, she was the outcast captain of the fae army. Then, a rebel prisoner.</p> <p>Now, the heir of the realm will come to take her rightful place on the throne—by blade, blood, and flame.</p> <p>Lia, Jace, and the rest of the Velyran rebels have thwarted the attack on Ellecaster, but with Kellan still on the run, they are forced to move their army into the safety of Alaia—the hidden sanctuary beyond the mountains. To end the century-long war and the evil queen whose power and iron fist grow each day, Lia will need to do more than just keep her wits about her. She'll need to seek out the unlikeliest and most dangerous of allies.</p> <p>Bonds will be formed, new enemies will be made, and sacrifices are inevitable. With the fate of Velyra on the line, they will rise to see its salvation… or fall in its demise.</p> <p>Throne of Glass <i>meets</i> House of the Dragon. <i>The Forbidden Heir Trilogy is a fun new take on fantasy, featuring enemies-to-lovers, unhinged banter, dragons, heartache, adventure, and dark sorcery that grows throughout the series. This is written in multiple first-person POVs, including the villains, and is a character-driven romantic fantasy. The story will be enjoyed by lovers of Sarah J. Maas, Jennifer L. Armentrout, and Carissa Broadbent.</i></p>"; 
